summary: Pokemon Card of the Day #1467: Lost Remover (Call of Legends)
title: Pokemon Card of the Day #1467: Lost Remover (Call of Legends)
body: Lost Remover was one of the few new Trainer cards worth using in Call of Legends, but it was pretty useful. When played, you got to put a Special Energy card attached to 1 of your opponent’s Pokemon into the Lost Zone. Not only was it a normal Trainer without the restrictions that Supporters had, but Double Colorless Energy, Rainbow Energy, and the later Prism Energy were all pretty common. Sure, there would be some decks based around things like Reshiram and Magnezone that didn’t care about this, but this gained value later in the HGSS-On format with all the Mewtwo EX and Tornadus running Double Colorless Energy. If you could fit it into a deck during that time, it was going to be a good choice.
